\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. M. pulegium} (Rochel) Bentham,{\i  Lab. Gen. Sp.} 382 (1834). Stems 20-50(-90) cm, erect, straight, usually simple, deflexed-puberulent or -pubescent. Leaves 10-30 × 5-20 mm, ovate, obtuse to acute, more or less crenate-dentate, shortly appressed pubescent, densely punctate beneath. Verticillasters with 10-70 flowers, lax, the lowest shorter and the upper longer than the subtending leaves. Calyx 3·5-4 mm, shortly pubescent, sparsely hairy in throat; teeth 1/3-1/2 as long as tube, linear-lanceolate or setaceous, equal. Corolla 7-9 mm, white or lilac. Nutlets obtuse. •{\i  S.W. Romania.} Rm.
\par

