\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. M. microphylla} (D'Urv.) Bentham,{\i  op. cit.} 377 (1834). Subglabrous to somewhat pubescent dwarf shrub 10-30 cm with more or less filiform, procumbent or ascending, often branched stems. Leaves 3-6 × 2-4 mm, triangular-ovate to elliptical, the upper sometimes narrowly elliptical, rounded or cuneate at base, acute, entire, flat, subsessile. Verticillasters with 1-6 usually erecto-patent flowers; peduncles or pedicels c. ½ as long as subtending leaves. Calyx 2·5-3·5 mm, patent-pubescent, villous in throat; teeth c. ½ as long as tube, lanceolate-acuminate to -subulate, unequal. Corolla 5-8 mm, purple. •{\i  S. Italy and Sicilia; Kriti and Karpathos.} ?Bl Cr It Si.
\par

